the idea of the move 6.f4 is block the long diagonal h8-a1 followed by e5, now black must be careful if 6....Bg7?.8.e5!-exd.9.fxd-Nfd7.10.e6 with big advantage for white , if 9...Ng4.10.Bb5+-Kf8.11.Ne6+and the black queen is lost so is the rest of the game . the correct move is 6...Nc6!.7.Nxc6-bxc.8.e5-Nd7.9.Be3-Bd7.10.Qf3......., the move 6....e5 is not so good because the important pawn d6 stays weak and it helps white to close the diagonal h8-a1 for the known DSB.

good move ,10.Bg5! pined the knight on f6 with pressure by Qf3 forcing black develop he's Pisces un comfortable.the move 10...Bg7? .11.Nd5-Nbd7.12.Rad1 and its hard to say how long the knight on f6 will stay alive .
